Project Planning List

Project Title: Library Management System
[x] Define the project's core functionality and purpose.
[x] Specify the use of JWT-based authentication for security.

Entity-Relationship Diagram (ERD):
[x]Create an ERD with entities: User, Book, Author, and Category.

User Stories:
 [x] Write user stories to describe key user interactions.
 [x] Specify JWT authentication for librarians and library members.


API Endpoints:

API Endpoints
User Authentication
POST /auth/users/register/: Register a new user with a username and password (Public)
POST /auth/users/login/: Log in and obtain a JWT token with a username and password (Public)
Books
POST /api/books/: Create a new book (Admin, requires JWT)
GET /api/books/: Get a list of all books (Public, does not require JWT)
GET /api/books/{id}: Get details of a book by ID (Public, does not require JWT)
PUT /api/books/{id}: Update book details (Admin, requires JWT)
DELETE /api/books/{id}: Delete a book (Admin, requires JWT)
Authors
POST /api/authors/: Create a new author (Admin, requires JWT)
GET /api/authors/: Get a list of all authors (Public, does not require JWT)
GET /api/authors/{id}: Get details of an author by ID (Public, does not require JWT)
PUT /api/authors/{id}: Update author details (Admin, requires JWT)
DELETE /api/authors/{id}: Delete an author (Admin, requires JWT)
Categories
POST /api/categories/: Create a new category (Admin, requires JWT)
GET /api/categories/: Get a list of all categories (Public, does not require JWT)
GET /api/categories/{id}: Get details of a category by ID (Public, does not require JWT)
PUT /api/categories/{id}: Update category details (Admin, requires JWT)
DELETE /api/categories/{id}: Delete a category (Admin, requires JWT)
Borrowing and Returning
POST /api/borrow/{bookId}: Borrow a book (Library Member, requires JWT)
POST /api/return/{bookId}: Return a book (Library Member, requires JWT)

[]Design API endpoints for user authentication, managing books, authors, categories, and borrowing/returning books.
[]Define access control (Admin, Public, Library Member) and JWT requirements for each endpoint.

